children.comment:
The [TransitionFunction] class provides common transition functions used for
[Transition] and [Tween] animations.

A transition function takes the [ratio] which is in the range from 0.0 to 1.0
and calculates the progress of the transitions.

The most simple transition function is a linear transition:
    var linear = (ratio) => ratio;

Overview of all available transition types:
<http://www.dartflash.com/docs/juggler/transitions.html>

children.comment:
An annotation used to mark an API as being experimental.

An API is considered to be experimental if it is still going through the
process of stabilizing and is subject to change or removal.

See also:

* [W3C recommendation](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W3C_recommendation)
children.name: Experimental

children.comment:
An annotation used to mark a feature as only being supported by a subset
of the browsers that Dart supports by default.

If an API is not annotated with [SupportedBrowser] then it is assumed to
work on all browsers Dart supports.
children.name: SupportedBrowser
